Process called "mips64_SYS_IOCTL" returns Integer:
    Note:
    SYS_IOCTL on MIPS64 n64 = 5015.
    Source: Linux kernel arch/mips/include/uapi/asm/unistd.h
    (n64 syscall table, 5000-base; __NR_ioctl = 5015).
    The previous value 15 was a 5000-base bookkeeping bug — the n64
    ABI uses the full absolute syscall number, NOT the offset within
    the table. Routing an ioctl call through 15 would either hit the
    o32 SYS_ioctl-equivalent slot (which is unused on n64 and
    returns -ENOSYS) or, worse, dispatch to whatever n64 syscall lives
    at table-entry 15, corrupting random kernel state. Closes the
    CSF-1 console_primitive dispatcher gap which calls SYS_IOCTL via
    syscall_ioctl for TCGETS / TIOCGWINSZ on MIPS64 targets.
    :End Note
    Return 5015
End Process

